sentence: Fastenal Company ( FAST ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 22, 2016.
A cash dividend payment of $0.3 per share is scheduled to be paid on August 23, 2016.
Shareholders who purchased FAST prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment.
This marks the 3rd quarter that FAST has paid the same dividend.
At the current stock price of $42.55, the dividend yield is 2.82%.
The previous trading day's last sale of FAST was $42.55, representing a -14.88% decrease from the 52 week high of $49.99 and a 23.51% increase over the 52 week low of $34.45.
FAST is a part of the Consumer Services sector, which includes companies such as Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) and Lowe's Companies, Inc. ( LOW ).
FAST's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $1.75.
Zacks Investment Research reports FAST's forecasted earnings growth in 2016 as -.85%, compared to an industry average of 26.7%.
For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the FAST Dividend History page.
